          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1606140105419-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the<strong> quinoa </strong>in a sieve under cold running water</p><p>Add the<strong> quinoa </strong>to the reserved pot with 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]<strong> </span>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the quinoa is tender</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and leave to steam-dry, uncovered, until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1606140112717-x200.jpg",
